Steps to do to convert video:
1. [ ] Add a command arg for video (e.g ivscii video [OPTIONS])
2. [ ] Probe the video file and get informations such as:
   - width
   - height
   = size
   - amount of frames
   - fps
   - duration
3. [ ] run ffmpeg on worker threads to decode the video and output the raw RGB values to a pipe (use image2pipe?)
4. [ ] the worker threads will also convert the RGBs into an ASCII art
5. [ ] when each thread has finished coverting, do a memcpy to a buffer
6. [ ] this buffer will be used by another thread that joins the conversion result of N-1 thread together.
7. [ ] this thread will compress the result using LZ4? and write the compressed data into a file

Possible issues:
1. - Threads that does the conversion is too slow and the join thread will starve of data
   - Possible solution: wait for data until all threads has finished executing, even if the buffer is empty. sleep for a milisecond to prevent this thread from polling too much


